In 12-inch non-stick fry pan, over medium heat, saute onions and garlic in oil 2 minutes. Add mushrooms and saute 4 minutes longer or until mushrooms are just tender. Remove from heat. Using metal blade, coarsely chop pecans in food processor. Add KELLOGG'S* RICE KRISPIES* cereal, rice, green pepper, carrots, seasonings and mushroom mixture. Pulse processor about 15 seconds or until mixture is a mealy consistency. Remove to mixing bowl and stir in egg whites. Divide mixture into 6 portions, about 1/2 cup each and shape into patties. Place on baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Broil 6 inches from heat, about 5 minutes per side or until browned. Serve hot on buns with lettuce and tomato or with chutney, if desired.